## 2026-05-09 — C14: pgvector semantic search (branch `chore/claude-audit-tools`, commit `b32b215`)

Semantic search is live in production. Users searching "cozy apartment El Poblado with pool" now get apartments ranked by meaning (similarity 0.74), not just keyword matching.

### What shipped

**`ai-embed` edge function (new, v10).** Embeds apartments/events/restaurants via Gemini `gemini-embedding-001` with SHA-256 idempotency (skips unchanged entities), timing-safe `x-ai-embed-secret` auth, and 3× retry with backoff. Stores 768-dim vectors in `listing_embeddings`, `event_embeddings`, `restaurant_embeddings`. 116 entities embedded in production.

**`ai-search` edge function (rewrite, v42).** Full rewrite from deno.land/std imports to `npm:` specifiers + `Deno.serve`. Adds semantic mode: embeds the user's query with `outputDimensionality: 768` (Matryoshka truncation) then calls pgvector RPCs for cosine similarity ranking. Falls back to keyword extraction + SQL on any embedding failure.

**`outputDimensionality: 768` fix.** `gemini-embedding-001` now defaults to 3072 dims. Added `outputDimensionality: 768` to all Gemini embedding calls so query vectors match the stored 768-dim embeddings.

**Semantic search RPCs corrected.** `semantic_search_listings`, `semantic_search_events`, `semantic_search_restaurants` had wrong parameter names (`result_limit` / no `similarity_threshold`) and a hard-coded `distance < 0.40` that blocked all results. Replaced with `match_count`, `similarity_threshold` (default 0.3), and full column sets including `description`, `rating`, `primary_image_url`, `event_type`, `city`.

**DB audit findings (not yet migrated).** 22 foreign key columns missing indexes (performance risk). 28 tables missing comments. 3 minor naming violations. Migration ready; blocked by hook pending `MDEAI_ALLOW_MIGRATION_EDIT=1`.

### Verification

```
mode: semantic
[apartment] Poblado Cozy 2BR  similarity=0.747
[apartment] Modern 2BR El Poblado  similarity=0.737
[restaurant] Dos Santos Cantina  similarity=0.656
```

